## Business objective: To predict customers who have a high potential to churn from the business<br>
## Business result:  Reduce the time and effort required to identify potentially churning customers, enabling the business to offer appropriate packages or promotions to retain them in advance<br>
### Methodology: Logistic regression model

dataset = Databel.csv
Meta data
Customer ID = A unique identifier assigned to each customer
Churn Label = A classification tag in a dataset that indicates whether a customer has churned
Account Length (in months) = Membership duration (Month)
Local Calls = Number of domestic calls
Local Mins = Minutes of domestic calls
Intl Calls = Number of international calls
Intl Mins = Minutes of international calls
Intl Active = A classification tag in a dataset that indicates using international call
Intl Plan = A classification tag of package for international call
Extra International Charges = International overage charges
Customer Service Calls = Number of times contacted customer service
Avg Monthly GB Download = Average download usage in GB per month
Unlimited Data Plan = A classification tag that indicate using unlimited plan
Extra Data Charges = Overage usage
State = Customer’s state of residence
Phone Number = Customer phone number
Gender = Customer gender
Age = Customer age
Under 30 = Customer age under 30
Senior = A classification tag of customer
Group = A classification tag to classified all customer
Number of Customers in Group = Number of customer in each group
Device Protection & Online Backup = A classification tag of protection and backup
Contract Type = Type of service contract
Payment Method = Method of payment
Monthly Charge = Monthly subscription fee
Total Charges = Total outstanding service fees

